to the editor re acceptable nursing care editorial aug 7 the for profit nursing home industry is plagued with fraud and mismanagement operators have been repeatedly found guilty of stealing hundreds of millions of dollars from taxpayers while providing substandard care is n't it time we accept that warehousing the elderly in institutional settings is a failed experiment congress must change the medicare rules to allow families real long term care options we need to move toward community based care systems like small group homes adult foster care and home help programs we can save taxpayers money allow the elderly to age with dignity and make institutionalized nursing care an option of last resort james l wilkes ii tampa fla aug 8 2000 the writer is a lawyer who represents victims of nursing home abuse

